Title: Application Analyst
Job_Description:
Description:
*
About Denver Botanic Gardens*: Green inside and out, Denver Botanic Gardens was founded in 1951 and is considered one of the top botanical gardens in the United States and a pioneer in water conservation. Accredited by the American Alliance of Museums, The Gardens has a robust living plant collection, natural history collection and art collection along with temporary art exhibitions. The Gardens is a dynamic, 24-acre urban oasis in the heart of the city, offering unforgettable opportunities to flourish with unique garden experiences for the whole family – as well as world-class exhibitions, education, and plant conservation research programs.
For more information, visit us online at www.botanicgardens.org.
Denver Botanic Gardens is currently seeking a Full Time Application Analyst in our IT Department! Read below to see if the requirements might be a good fit for you:
The Application Analyst champions effective software utilization throughout the enterprise, supporting visitor-facing and back-office applications. The primary purpose of this role is enabling DBG employees and visitors to successfully utilize various software applications in fulfilling organizational objectives. The Application Analyst contributes to the organizational mission by maximizing usage of enterprise applications and information that ultimately lead to a transformative experience for our Garden visitors.

Title: Manager, Machine Learning
Job_Description:
About Inari...
Inari is the SEEDesign™ company. We embrace the diversity and complexity of nature in every aspect of our business to drive innovation – to push the boundaries of what is possible. Through our unrivaled technology platform, Inari uses predictive design and advanced multiplex gene editing to develop step-change products. We are taking a nature positive approach to unlock the full potential of seed that will transform the food system. The results will lead to more productive acres delivering value creation for farmers and a more sustainable future for our planet.
Our success is dependent on great minds, collaborating to generate bright ideas and deliver exceptional outcomes.
We have over 230 employees, with research sites in Cambridge, MA (USA) and Ghent (Belgium), as well as a product development site in West Lafayette, IN (USA). We've deliberately built a team that brings diversity of thought to all aspects of our business, to generate new ideas, approaches, and ways of operating. And we've intentionally combined experience with potential, bringing agriculture industry experts with the desire to innovate together with bright minds from academia, human therapeutics, software, and consulting. If you want to be part of a diverse and inclusive team developing unique solutions to feed the world while protecting our planet's natural resources, we'd love to hear from you!

Title: Manager, Machine Learning
Job_Description:
Principal Software Development Engineer (Job #)
About RMS Bellevue
RMS is building a cutting-edge risk management platform for the global risk market, enabling RMS’ clients to share, discover, and consume Petabytes of risk modeling and insurance data to produce big insights. This platform is known as Risk Intelligence.
The RMS Risk Intelligence SaaS platform enables software engineering teams at RMS to produce world-class risk models, and empowers our customers to consume and integrate the resulting analytical data in their business processes.
About the RMS AI/ML Team

Title: Manager, Machine Learning
Job_Description:
Are you an experienced, passionate pioneer in technology, with versatile leadership qualities and enthusiasm to tackle new and difficult problems? If so, then Raytheon BBN is the place for you.
Who we are
For more than 70 years, scientists and engineers in diverse disciplines at Raytheon BBN have collaborated to solve real-world problems through research, exploration, development and prototyping. We partner with the best technical talent in academia and industry to challenge the status quo, pioneer new technologies, and create transformative solutions.

The Opportunity
We are seeking an AI researcher with leadership and entrepreneurial experience, who prides themselves on their ingenuity, creativity, and resourcefulness to build a “next wave” innovative artificial intelligence (AI) research focus within our Analytics and Machine Intelligence group at BBN. The ideal candidate will have machine learning expertise as well as broad interdisciplinary knowledge. This will lead to leveraging existing technologies in our portfolio such as human language technologies and image processing capabilities into new domains and applications. The selected candidate will develop, propose, and carry out new research as a Principal Investigator on programs for the Defense Sector and the Intelligence Community.

Title: Manager, Machine Learning
Job_Description:
Who We Are

Boston Consulting Group partners with leaders in business and society to tackle their most important challenges and capture their greatest opportunities. BCG was the pioneer in business strategy when it was founded in 1963. Today, we help clients with total transformation-inspiring complex change, enabling organizations to grow, building competitive advantage, and driving bottom-line impact.

To succeed, organizations must blend digital and human capabilities. Our diverse, global teams bring deep industry and functional expertise and a range of perspectives to spark change. BCG delivers solutions through leading-edge management consulting along with technology and design, corporate and digital ventures—and business purpose. We work in a uniquely collaborative model across the firm and throughout all levels of the client organization, generating results that allow our clients to thrive.

Title: Manager, Machine Learning
Job_Description:
ABOUT PLACER.AI:
Placer.ai is a fast-growing big data startup led by seasoned executives and repeat entrepreneurs who are building the world's first "Google Analytics for the physical world." Placer.ai's platform provides instant visibility into any property in the U.S., presenting accurate details about visitation patterns and demographic breakdowns of visitors. Placer.ai's customers can see where visitors have been before, where they go afterwards, where they typically go for sports, entertainment, groceries, etc., and what their interests are. Placer.ai's A.I.-based SaaS platform replaces archaic solutions such as manual surveys, installed cameras and other people-counting systems, creating a blue ocean market of more than $100B.
Placer.ai has grown 3x year-over-year for the past 3 years, counting more than 1000 paying customers across a range of industries, including 2 of the world's top-10 retailers, 2 of the top-10 CPG firms worldwide, a world's top hospitality firm, 2 of the world's top-10 commercial real estate (CRE) firms and 2 of the world's top multinational asset managers and hedge funds. Placer.ai has just raised $100M for Unicorn ($1B+) valuation in Series C funding.

Title: Manager, Machine Learning
Job_Description:
About AutoGrid
The world’s leading energy companies turn to AutoGrid to integrate all distributed energy resources, turn on new revenue streams and drive deeper engagement with their customers. Our suite of Energy Internet applications allows utilities, electricity retailers, renewable energy project developers and energy service providers to deliver clean, affordable and reliable energy in a distributed energy world.
How do we do this? By pioneering the science of flexibility management. This innovative approach enables energy providers to mine the Energy Internet’s rich data lode to extract flexible capacity from distributed energy resources. In turn, flexible capacity can be used to balance energy supply and demand in real time, increase the productivity and value of energy assets, and deliver new energy services to customers

We are a global leader in food & beverage ingredients. Pioneers at heart, we operate at the forefront of consumer trends to provide food & beverage manufacturers with products and ingredients that will delight their consumers. Making a positive impact on people and planet is all part of the delight. With a deep-rooted presence in the countries where our ingredients are grown, we are closer to farmers, enabling better quality, and more reliable, traceable and transparent supply. Title: Commerce Specialist 2 - Community Capital Facilities [14015]
Job_Description:
Description
Apply Early! First review of applications begins 10/5/2022.

This Commerce Specialist 2 provides support to the Community Capital Facilities Unit (CCF). The CCF unit funds non-residential community facility projects that provide a variety of public benefits through multiple state funded programs. This position supports the CCF Property Securitization Manager with tasks associated with the securitization of CCF grants. This position also supports the CCF by acting as the lead subject matter expert for the Commerce Contract Management System (CMS) and data analysis as it pertaining to CCF grants.

This recruitment may be used to fill future vacancies that occur over the next 60 days.

Title: Commerce Specialist 2 - Community Capital Facilities [14015]
Job_Description:
Company TriHealth, Inc.
Location Cincinnati, Ohio
Reporting Relationship The Senior Vice President/Chief Human Resources Officer will report to the President and CEO of TriHealth, Inc., Mr. Mark Clement.
Website https://www.trihealth.com/

ORGANIZATION BACKGROUND/CULTURE

With 13,000 team members, TriHealth is the Cincinnati region’s only integrated delivery system and the third-largest employer, with five hospitals and nearly 140 other ambulatory, post-acute, and other care sites throughout Ohio, Kentucky and Indiana. Its more than 600 employed physicians and independent medical staff of more than 1,800 physicians care for more than 600,000 members of the community.
TriHealth also operates the largest corporate health and fitness program in Greater Cincinnati, the largest not-for-profit hospice in the region, the largest free health center, and significant teaching programs, including nine residencies and fellowships. TriHealth’s Hatton Research Institute directs an active medical research program and a comprehensive academic program. Since 1896, The Good Samaritan College of Nursing and Health Science has provided quality nursing education.

Title: Commerce Specialist 2 - Community Capital Facilities [14015]
Job_Description:
Description


This position will work directly with the Asset Management Supervisor to oversee the management of approximately 400 loans with scheduled payments generating $3M+ in revenue annually for the state’s Housing Trust Fund Repayment Account (Fund 532). The position will handle property accounting, monthly invoicing, monthly reconciliation, re-amortization calculations, final payoffs, and contract closeouts for MHU.

The position will assist with maintaining repayment policies in partnership with the Commerce Specialist 4, and work with managers, and necessary staff to ensure state policy is followed, and that loan work-outs are conducted in a fair and equitable manner. The position will recommend and maintain internal loan monitoring practices, train staff on the Contract Management System (CMS), track and reconcile revenue for the unit in partnership with Commerce’s Accounting Office. The position will be the internal team member most often interfacing with accounting staff from vendors to explain Commerce practices and to track revenue.


This recruitment may be used to fill future vacancies that occur over the next 60 days.

Title: Commerce Specialist 2 - Community Capital Facilities [14015]
Job_Description:
Description


This position works in the Multifamily Housing Unit (MHU) of HD, with the state Housing Trust Fund (HTF) and the federal HOME and National Housing Trust Fund (NHTF) programs. This position is responsible for preparing, reviewing, and maintaining complex contract and legal documents to protect state interests in capital investments made through the MHU programs, and provides technical assistance to program contractors and to other MHU staff regarding agency contracting requirements, program loan terms, and related legal documents.

This recruitment may be used to fill future vacancies that occur over the next 90 days.

Title: Machine Learning Engineering Lead
Job_Description:
At Bristol Myers Squibb, we are inspired by a single vision – transforming patients’ lives through science. In oncology, hematology, immunology and cardiovascular disease – and one of the most diverse and promising pipelines in the industry – each of our passionate colleagues contribute to innovations that drive meaningful change. We bring a human touch to every treatment we pioneer. Join us and make a difference.
Summary:
Machine Learning (ML) Engineering and Operations is a new team in the Enterprise Data Platforms area, focused on operationalizing machine learning models and enabling ML solutions at scale. We are looking for a passionate technical leader with a proven track record delivering machine learning solutions at scale and well versed in the growing field of Machine Learning Operations (MLOps).

Title: Machine Learning Engineering Lead
Job_Description:
About Inari...
Inari is the SEEDesign™ company. We embrace the diversity and complexity of nature in every aspect of our business to drive innovation – to push the boundaries of what is possible. Through our unrivaled technology platform, Inari uses predictive design and advanced multiplex gene editing to develop step-change products. We are taking a nature positive approach to unlock the full potential of seed that will transform the food system. The results will lead to more productive acres delivering value creation for farmers and a more sustainable future for our planet.
Our success is dependent on great minds, collaborating to generate bright ideas and deliver exceptional outcomes.
We have over 230 employees, with research sites in Cambridge, MA (USA) and Ghent (Belgium), as well as a product development site in West Lafayette, IN (USA). We've deliberately built a team that brings diversity of thought to all aspects of our business, to generate new ideas, approaches, and ways of operating. And we've intentionally combined experience with potential, bringing agriculture industry experts with the desire to innovate together with bright minds from academia, human therapeutics, software, and consulting. If you want to be part of a diverse and inclusive team developing unique solutions to feed the world while protecting our planet's natural resources, we'd love to hear from you!

Title: Machine Learning Engineering Lead
Job_Description:
Principal Software Development Engineer (Job #)
About RMS Bellevue
RMS is building a cutting-edge risk management platform for the global risk market, enabling RMS’ clients to share, discover, and consume Petabytes of risk modeling and insurance data to produce big insights. This platform is known as Risk Intelligence.
The RMS Risk Intelligence SaaS platform enables software engineering teams at RMS to produce world-class risk models, and empowers our customers to consume and integrate the resulting analytical data in their business processes.
About the RMS AI/ML Team

Title: Machine Learning Engineering Lead
Job_Description:
About RMS Bellevue
RMS is building a cutting-edge risk management platform for the global risk market, enabling RMS’ clients to share, discover, and consume Petabytes of risk modeling and insurance data to produce big insights. We enable teams at RMS to produce world-class risk models, and our customers to consume and integrate the resulting analytical data in their business processes. On top of this platform, we are developing innovative products with state-of-the-art user experiences. We’re looking for top engineers to help us drive this vision forward and we are only beginning.
About the Platform Services Team
The RMS Bellevue team is growing the Platform Services Team that is responsible for end-to-end management of tenant lifecycle that is the building block of RMS’ SaaS offering. Our team’s charter is to provide the best-in-class multitenant management SaaS platform called Service Management Layer (which supports authentication, subscription, quotas, resources, usage metrics and billing). We launched our initial version in summer of 2020, and we are busy lighting up new capabilities and delighting our customers. Our team is responsible for automating the entire stack of high performance, large scale, geographically dispersed resources throughout its lifecycle. This is a technology stack that will challenge you and diversify your skills. If you are someone who has an appetite to work on these areas and want to work with a great team in a fast paced yet fun filled environment that loves challenges, we would love to talk to you.
